  "rai:dataCollection": "SERS serum spectra collected using the SERSome methodology from 424 participants (PCa, BPH, and controls; all male; ages 41–89). Fasting venous blood collected; serum ultrafiltered through a 3-kDa cutoff membrane (Millipore, Amicon Ultra-4) to isolate small metabolites. Citrate-reduced Ag NPs (~61 nm TEM diameter) mixed with filtered metabolites at 1:1 vol:vol ratio; 200 spectra per SERSome acquired on a Horiba XploRA INV confocal Raman system (638 nm laser, 12.67 mW, 10× objective, quartz capillary ID 1 mm / OD 2 mm), 10 µm step size. 724 data points per spectrum, spectral range 600–1800 cm⁻¹.",
  "rai:dataCollectionType": "Direct measurement",
  "rai:dataPreprocessingProtocol": "Baseline removal applied using LabSpec 6 software (polynomial method, degree 10, max 200 points). Raw spectra stored as PyTorch tensor files organised by class label.",
  "rai:dataAnnotationProtocol": "Class labels (PCa, BPH, control) assigned by clinical diagnosis confirmed by transrectal prostate biopsy with H&E staining and Gleason scoring. T stage and N stage determined by urologists per AJCC 8th staging system. Participants enrolled at Ren Ji Hospital, School of Medicine, Shanghai Jiao Tong University. Ethics approval obtained (KY2021-030).",
  "rai:personalSensitiveInformation": "Spectra are derived from human blood serum of clinical patients. No direct patient identifiers are included, but biological measurements constitute sensitive health-related data under applicable data-protection regulations. Ethics approval obtained from Ren Ji Hospital, SJTU School of Medicine (KY2021-030).",
  "rai:dataBiases": "All participants are male (biologically); dataset is specific to prostate cancer and does not generalise to other tumour types or female populations. Recruitment from two hospital systems in Shanghai and one in Ningbo/Jiading; geographic and demographic diversity is limited to eastern China. Age range 41–89 years; very young or elderly populations are not represented.",
  "rai:dataLimitations": "Diagnostic accuracy of 80.8% (internal test set) and 73% (external validation) requires further improvement before clinical deployment. Performance may differ with varying Ag NP batches, serum collection protocols, or Raman instrument configurations. External validation cohorts are also China-based; generalisability to other ethnicities and healthcare systems has not been established.",
  "rai:dataSocialImpact": "Serum SERS metabolomics for prostate cancer screening offers a minimally invasive alternative to PSA testing or tissue biopsy. Key serum biomarkers identified include uric acid, hypoxanthine, uracil, and tryptamine. Diagnostic results must be validated by qualified healthcare professionals before any clinical application.",
  "rai:dataUseCases": "Multiclass classification (PCa vs. BPH vs. control); serum metabolic biomarker discovery; development and benchmarking of spectral deep learning models for cancer diagnostics; Gleason score prediction.",
  "rai:hasSyntheticData": false,
  "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "Data collection: Laboratory measurements on human biological samples (blood serum, saliva, tissue biopsies) collected under clinical or research protocols. Preprocessing: Spectra are provided with class labels. Any preprocessing applied (baseline correction, smoothing, normalisation) is described in the source publication. Annotation: Class labels assigned based on known sample identity or validated analytical reference methods.",
  "prov:wasDerivedFrom": "https://figshare.com/articles/dataset/ComFilE_for_PCa/28107395"
}